- SiO2, Na2O, ZnO, and La2O3 are oxide concentrations in glass samples, which contribute to the glass's properties such as durability, clarity, and refractive index;
- The term "elite members" refers to glass samples with the highest SiO2 concentration within their respective series;
- "Elemental wisdom" is a metaphor for the sum of the concentrations of SiO2, Na2O, ZnO, and La2O3;
